document_data.History:
None remembered the civilization that had built the ancient ziggurats that dominated the Old City.{{Cite adventurers league/Peril at the Port|32}}

During the events of the [[death curse]],{{ToA-time}} a strange series of disappearances struck the Old City in which people would hear the "[[Call of the Dead]]"&mdash;causing them to mumble to themselves about [[Viplo|"Death"]] summoning them&mdash;before vanishing and sometimes reappearing as a [[zombie]] days later. These events led [[Alastar Bol]], a representative of the [[Order of the Gauntlet]] in Port Nyanzaru, to send a [[priest]] named [[Derio]] to investigate.

Following the end of the death curse, undead began to proliferate in the refuse pit, and soon threatened the folk of the Old City.{{Cite adventurers league/Putting the Dead to Rest|3}} This was caused by a [[wight]] [[necromancer]] named [[Jaru Tasca]], who plotted to use a piece of the [[Cyst]]&mdash;a powerful [[necromantic]] mass of flesh&mdash;to transform Port Nyanzaru's residents and [[adventurer]]s into undead. Her minions would rise from the refuse pit to capture victims and return them to her secret base in the catacombs beneath the Old City.{{Cite adventurers league/Fester and Burn|3}}

Inhabitants.Notable Inhabitants:
* [[Favin Kreeger]], a cowardly [[albino dwarf]] who was paid to hide bodies in the Refuse Pit during the late 15{{th}} century DR.{{Cite adventurers league/Fester and Burn|4-5}}
* [[Jaha Mubsie]], an enforcer for the beggar prince Pock-Marked Po in the late 15{{th}} century DR. He had a [[flying monkey]] companion named [[Uku the Spider Boy]].
* [[Miboro Yan]], the much-beloved proprietor of the Holdup tavern in the late 15{{th}} century DR.
* [[Pock-Marked Po]], the so-called "Hideous Prince" of the Old City who lived in a deceptively luxurious hut as of the late 15{{th}} century DR.{{Cite adventurers league/A City on the Edge|15}}
* [[Viplo]], a [[halfling]] [[mage]] who lived adjacent to the southernmost ziggurat as of the late 15{{th}} century DR.
